    <string name="about_info_text">This application is part of a student Final Year Project. It allows you to search for location-based crime data.</string>
    <string name="about_instructions_text">
        To use the app, first select a crime-location relationship to use as a basis for a search.
        This means you will be search for certain types of crimes in the vicinity of certain locations.
        This will take you to a map view. Pressing on the map will create a search for location based crime data.
        Results can be view on the map or in a list by toggling map/list view button in the navigation bar. Locations are comparatively ranked.
        Selecting a location opens a details view. A save feature is also available to store search results.
    </string>
    <string name="about_crime_badge_desc">
